top_stories.title: XRobotics’ countertop robots are cooking up 25,000 pizzas a month
top_stories.description: XRobotics recently raised a $2.5 million seed round to help it produce more of its countertop pizza robots.
top_stories.author: Rebecca Szkutak

top_stories.title: Anthropic’s AI-generated blog dies an early death
top_stories.description: Anthropic was experimenting with an AI-generated blog. TechCrunch profiled it. Then, Anthropic shut it down.
top_stories.author: Kyle Wiggers

top_stories.title: Qualcomm to acquire semiconductor firm Alphawave Semi for $2.4B
top_stories.description: Qualcomm has acquired Alphawave Semi, a U.K.-based semiconductor company focused on high-speed data center connectivity, for around $2.4 billion.
top_stories.author: Kyle Wiggers

top_stories.title: OpenAI updates ChatGPT’s voice mode with more natural-sounding speech
top_stories.description: ChatGPT's natural-sounding voice mode just got a big update, including more natural-sounding synthetic voice options.
top_stories.author: Kyle Wiggers

top_stories.title: UK Prime Minister, NVIDIA CEO Set the Stage as AI Lights Up Europe
top_stories.description:
AI isn’t waiting. And this week, neither is Europe. At London’s Olympia, under a ceiling of steel beams and enveloped by the thrum of startup pitches, it didn’t feel like the start of a conference — it felt like the start of something bigger.
